10271580@unknown@formal@none@1@S@In 2002, Linux coordinator [[Linus Torvalds]] decided to use BitKeeper to develop the Linux kernel, a free software project, claiming no free software alternative met his needs.@1@27@@oe@30-11-2008
10271590@unknown@formal@none@1@S@This controversial decision drew criticism from several sources, including the Free Software Foundation's founder Richard Stallman.@1@16@@oe@30-11-2008
